text:
(1)
2-8 James Slip, east side, south from and including Cherry to Water Streets. The buildings on the extreme right is No. 364 Water Street and is at the N.E. corner of James Slip. Shown on the left are Nos. 81 to 97 Cherry Street, south side, east from James Slip to but not including Oliver Street. The 4-story corner building prominently shown in the foreground is No. 2 James slip and No. 81 Cherry Street.
September 7, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, showing the houses in reverse order, i.e., 8 to 2. Also shown are Nos. 364 to 370 Water Street (right), at, adjoining and east of the N.E. corner of James Slip.
May 3, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: James Slip - Cherry Street
